M|dev|When a fix is ready to ship:
M|dev|1. Present ONE brief: "Ready to deploy — [what's changing in 1 line]. Commit + push to prod + run migrations if needed. Go?"
M|dev|2. Wait for ap
M|dev|3. Execute fully: `git add [files]` → `git commit` → `git push` → `npm run db:migrate` (if migrations changed)
M|dev|4. Report result
M|dev|Never re-ask mid-dpl. Owner is not always present — autonomous deploy on ap is the expected behaviour.
M|dev|Destructive operations (DROP TABLE, data deletion, force-push) still require explicit confirmation regardless.